# UVA Law - Intro to Law & Business Study System

Complete study system for UVA Law's Introduction to Law & Business course.

## 🎓 What's Included

- **7 Complete Lessons** - One HTML file per class with full content
- **Shared Styling** - Professional UVA-branded CSS
- **GitHub Pages Ready** - Upload and go!

## 📁 File Structure

```
uva-law-study-site/
├── index.html          # Home page with all class cards
├── class1.html         # Financial Statements (cupcake problem, accrual accounting)
├── class2.html         # Transaction Costs (Boeing/Spirit, Coase theorem)
├── class3.html         # Entity Choice (C-Corp vs LLC, tax calculations)
├── class4.html         # VC Finance (Series B problem, cap tables)
├── class5.html         # Term Sheets (liquidation prefs, all terms)
├── class6.html         # Contracts (BSC/Medinol relational contract)
├── class7.html         # M&A (strategic vs financial, discount rates)
├── styles.css          # Shared styling for all pages
└── README.md           # This file
```

## 🚀 How to Deploy to GitHub Pages

1. **Create a new GitHub repository**
   - Go to github.com → New repository
   - Name it something like `uva-law-study`
   - Make it public (for GitHub Pages to work free)

2. **Upload all files**
   - Drag and drop this entire folder into the repo
   - OR use git:
     ```bash
     git init
     git add .
     git commit -m "Initial commit"
     git remote add origin YOUR_REPO_URL
     git push -u origin main
     ```

3. **Enable GitHub Pages**
   - Go to Settings → Pages
   - Source: Deploy from a branch
   - Branch: `main` / `root`
   - Save

4. **Done!**
   - Your site will be at: `https://yourusername.github.io/repo-name`
   - Takes 1-2 minutes to build first time

